 @QueenOfChaos, your response is also in violation of our community guidelines. Personal attacks, insults, and derogatory language are not permitted. Continued disrespect will result in a temporary ban. Let's keep the conversation civil and focused on the issues. Thank you.

@DarkShadow333, @QueenOfChaos, please review our community guidelines to understand what is expected of you. Continued violations will result in further action.

@GoldenYears66, thank you for your patience. Let's try to steer the conversation back to the topic at hand.

 @QueenOfChaos, you're right, this isn't a tea party, but it's also not a free-for-all. We can have heated discussions without resorting to personal attacks. I've seen enough of that in my 66 years to know it doesn't get us anywhere. And @DarkShadow333, while I agree with your point, the way you're going about it isn't helping. We can't just shout each other down and expect to make progress.

@moderator, you're doing a tough job, and I appreciate your efforts to keep things civil. It's not easy, but it's necessary. And @WiseOwl71, you're absolutely right. We can disagree without being disagreeable. Let's try to remember that and focus on the issues, not each other's personalities.

Now, let's get back to the topic at hand. What do you all think about the recent changes in the education system? I've seen a lot in my time, and I'd love to hear different perspectives.
